<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[2061,2653,2232,2654]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heim de Balsac" authorityYear="1936" box="[2061,2256,2346,2380]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="seurati">Acomys seurati</taxonomicName>
1s sometimes considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Desmarest" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[2241,2405,2385,2419]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Acomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cahirinus">A. cahirinus</taxonomicName>
, but their karyotypes and dental morphologies differ.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[2061,2653,2232,2654]" box="[2062,2218,2468,2497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Monotypic.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6898483" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6898483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6898483/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" startId="3.[2061,2233,2503,2537]" targetBox="[1446,2037,2235,2649]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[2061,2653,2232,2654]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2061,2237,2503,2537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Distribution.</emphasis>
Mouydir, Tassili, and Hoggar Mts in Sahara Desert, S Algeria.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[2061,2653,2232,2654]" lastBlockId="3.[1447,2653,2660,3087]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2061,2310,2582,2616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head—body 87-99 mm, tail 105-125 mm, ear 17-5-21-5 mm, hindfoot 17-20 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 38, FN = 68.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[1447,2653,2660,3087]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1448,1560,2739,2773]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Habitat.</emphasis>
Rocky areas in desert of southern Algeria at elevations of 1000-2000 m. Seurat’s Spiny Mice rest in crevices or under rocks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
